    "Moreover, contextualizing classification instances improves performance, especially for the primary classes, and further closes the gap to full models.",
    "We found in S 3 that in case of limited computing resources, prompting methods allow practitioners to employ smaller PLMs in a few-shot scenario, while achieving classification results comparable to larger models.",
    "However, free-text sections, such as Anamnese, may still benefit from larger model architectures (Fig. 7).",
    "Finally, in S 4, we addressed the need for transparent and trustworthy model predictions in low-resource German clinical NLP, and possible use cases for interpretability methods.",
    "Our study demonstrates that the analysis of Shapley values can help improve training data quality, which is especially important with small shot sizes."
